  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.10.2-stable`\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\nCommit hash : 97d11b0187b4695ccf44e3b71b54155fe405a36f\r\n```\r\nGeth\r\nVersion: \r\nGit Commit: 97d11b0187b4695ccf44e3b71b54155fe405a36f\r\nGit Commit Date: 20210408\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nGo Version: go1.16.3\r\nOperating System: linux\r\nGOPATH=\r\nGOROOT=go\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nCan send ETH\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nSent ETH or any token will return this error:\r\n> chain not synced beyond EIP-155 replay-protection fork block\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nUse docker image: \r\n```\r\nimage: ethereum/client-go:alltools-stable\r\nentrypoint: [\"geth\"]\r\n```\r\nto start a eth node\r\n\r\nAfter sync is done (not sure - but currently the syncing process is updated regularly):\r\n\r\nThen do transfer coin from a address to another address\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\nI don't know how to get backtrace\r\n````\r\n\r\n\r\nMy eth sync progress:\r\n\r\nStart: 2021-04-14\r\nCurrent: 2021-04-24\r\nI used fast sync:\r\n\r\n```\r\n> eth.syncing\r\n{\r\n  currentBlock: 12302237,\r\n  highestBlock: 12302312,\r\n  knownStates: 165739095,\r\n  pulledStates: 165657294,\r\n  startingBlock: 12285779\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI tried to add: `--rpc.allow-unprotected-txs` arguments to allow EIP-155 but the error does not go away.\r\n\r\n\r\nCan anyone point me out some ideas to pass through this issue?\r\n",
